00:00:06.839 --> 00:00:07.180
Mountain Ranch Resort

00:00:07.180 --> 00:00:12.690
Hey Guys, Mike with Mike's Road Trip here
in Northern Arizona staying at the Mountain

00:00:12.690 --> 00:00:19.690
Ranch resort at Beacon Hill, which is located
just outside of Williams, a historic Route

00:00:19.949 --> 00:00:26.949
66 town known as the gateway to the Grand
Canyon, so come along with me and let me show

00:00:34.590 --> 00:00:36.390
you around...

00:00:36.390 --> 00:00:40.870
As soon as you walk into the lobby, you'll
be warmly greeted by the staff, many of whom

00:00:40.870 --> 00:00:44.450
are the owners and their family.

00:00:44.450 --> 00:00:51.450
Guests have two accommodation option...a standard
room, or the superior, which has upgraded

00:00:51.879 --> 00:00:58.039
furniture and some unites have a microwave
with mini fridge...perfect for those extended

00:00:58.039 --> 00:01:00.739
stays.

00:01:00.739 --> 00:01:05.899
Back in the lobby you can pick up some brochures
for area attractions, or take a stroll through

00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:11.670
the boutique...

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:17.689
One you've gotten settled, you can take in
any number of on-site activities...from tennis,

00:01:17.689 --> 00:01:24.689
hoops, horseshoes, volley ball, to swimming.

00:01:30.329 --> 00:01:34.639
At the back of the property is the entrance
to the Kaibab National Forest, where you can

00:01:34.639 --> 00:01:41.639
go hiking, take out a complimentary mountain
bike, or... go horseback riding...

00:01:49.209 --> 00:01:54.060
Just a few miles from the Resort are a number
of other activities to consider...such as

00:01:54.060 --> 00:01:59.299
the Grand Canyon Rail way, which leaves from
downtown Williams and takes passengers up

00:01:59.299 --> 00:02:04.319
to the Canyon.

00:02:04.319 --> 00:02:10.149
After your trip you can stroll the historic
streets of Route 66

00:02:10.149 --> 00:02:14.620
If you don't feel like taking the train, you
can drive to the South Rim to take in the

00:02:14.620 --> 00:02:19.049
awe-inspiring sight.

00:02:19.049 --> 00:02:26.049
Just a few miles from the resort is an extraordinary
wildlife attraction called, Bearziona.

00:02:39.540 --> 00:02:44.730
Back at the resort...I mentioned they place
an emphasis on health and well being...and

00:02:44.730 --> 00:02:50.650
that starts at the Ranch Restaurant, where
you'll find an outstanding menu of all natural,

00:02:50.650 --> 00:02:57.079
organic when possible, menu items. No processed
foods are used and everything is made fresh

00:02:57.079 --> 00:03:04.079
daily.

00:03:21.030 --> 00:03:26.239
Included in your stay is the most important
meal of the day...breakfast consists of fresh

00:03:26.239 --> 00:03:33.239
fruit and baked goods along with a made-to-order
omelet or a whole grain Belgium waffle.

00:03:35.670 --> 00:03:42.670
After breakfast you can burn those calories
off with an intense functional fitness workout.

00:03:43.379 --> 00:03:50.379
Well, that's it from the Mountain Ranch Resort...until
next time, we'll see ya on the road.

00:03:51.459 --> 00:03:51.930
Mountain Ranch Resort is located in Williams, Arizona and is at the gateway to the Grand Canyon

00:03:51.930 --> 00:03:53.930
 

